    <li id="fn:16" role="doc-endnote">
      <p>According to Crate Digging Cooperative Records, the term <em>crate
digger</em> originates in hip-hop culture, specifically with the DJ
practice of utilizing literal milk crates to transport and store
vinyl records. ‚ÄúCrate digging‚Äù is the active, physical, often
voracious scouring of record stores in search for vinyl records ‚Äúto
sample.‚Äù More recently, the term has loosened to include internet
searches, digital downloads, video watching, and any activity that
allows you to engage in a ‚Äúself discovery of music.‚Äù rchecka, ‚ÄúCrate
Digging (Re)Defined,‚Äù Crate Digging Cooperative,
<a href="http://cratedigging.co/cratedigging.htm">http://cratedigging.co/cratedigging.htm</a>.¬†<a href="#fnref:16" class="reversefootnote" role="doc-backlink">&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;</a></p>
