<a href="%20https:/www.youtube.com/watch?v=3xum1CIiSxI">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3xum1CIiSxI</a>.
Clive Chin, one of the founders of ‚Äúdub,‚Äù has worked as a musician
and producer with the Wailers, Dennis Brown, Lee ‚ÄúScratch‚Äù Perry,
Black Uhuru, and Gregory Isaacs, among others. The Shelter, one of
Shanghai‚Äôs most popular clubs, was established by local DJ Gary Wang
and expat Gareth Williams and operated in Shanghai‚Äôs French
Concession from 2007 to its closing in late 2016. The club was
housed in a renovated bomb shelter, one of over two thousand built
during the 1950s by the Chinese government in response to the threat
of Soviet encroachment, and was known for playing roots reggae,
dancehall, and dubstep and for promoting local music. See Gareth
Williams, ‚ÄúCutting Edge Music Finds a Home in Shanghai at the
Shelter,‚Äù <em>Electronic Beats</em>, 24 June 2016,
<a href="https://www.electronicbeats.net/club-feature-shelter-shanghai/">https://www.electronicbeats.net/club-feature-shelter-shanghai/</a>.¬†<a href="#fnref:36" class="reversefootnote" role="doc-backlink">&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;</a></p>
